The paper discusses a methodology for generating personalized feedback for online programming lessons and contests, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The methodology involves clustering submissions and verifying them against instructor-validated submissions, which involves techniques from programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses a novel algorithm for generating feedback, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper focuses on improving the quality of feedback for students, which falls under the category of computer science education (cs.EDU).
